      • asyncCommit

        public ActionCallback asyncCommit()
        Returns:
        callback which is set to ActionCallback.setDone() when the tree structure is committed. By default it just calls commit() synchronously but it is desirable to override it to provide asynchronous commit to the tree structure to make it more responsible. E.g. when you should commit all documents during the commit(), you can use asyncCommitDocuments(Project) to do it asynchronously.
